			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Very loosely written article, though some of the comments are written well. I disagree , writers block does exist. One of the comment says, that it need not be in medical profession as its not creative, I strongly disagree. On the contrary even doctors and surgeons or even mechanic can have block, so is with  any other creative field and field that is evolving and changing. Surgeon can have a block not necessarily in a particular case, but occasionally one can loose faith in their abilities,that is a block! So everyone once in a while may have a block in the thought process. Comprehending writers block in just one dimension or linear fashion may lead to such blogs.</p>
