					<description><![CDATA[I don&#039;t have and have never had a broken bone, but that does not mean one can&#039;t break a bone.  There was even a point in my life when I was completely convinced I&#039;d broken my hand, but it turned out I hadn&#039;t.  My nephew, on the other hand, did break his hand about a week ago.  Broken bones exist.  I have been blessed to have never been the recipient of such, but they really do happen.

When writers who have been fortunate enough to never really been crippled by writers block blithely singsong on the internet that there&#039;s no such thing, I often wonder how many other things they assume don&#039;t exist just because it hasn&#039;t happened to them.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I don&#8217;t have and have never had a broken bone, but that does not mean one can&#8217;t break a bone.  There was even a point in my life when I was completely convinced I&#8217;d broken my hand, but it turned out I hadn&#8217;t.  My nephew, on the other hand, did break his hand about a week ago.  Broken bones exist.  I have been blessed to have never been the recipient of such, but they really do happen.</p>
<p>When writers who have been fortunate enough to never really been crippled by writers block blithely singsong on the internet that there&#8217;s no such thing, I often wonder how many other things they assume don&#8217;t exist just because it hasn&#8217;t happened to them.</p>
